1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,542
It's like walking into
an office or a court

2
00:00:03,567 --> 00:00:07,890
Same thing, like now
when we enter the court

3
00:00:08,047 --> 00:00:10,130
There are people and
there are ISIS members

4
00:00:10,911 --> 00:00:14,219
There are visitors coming for
identity cards and other matters

5
00:00:14,714 --> 00:00:16,927
All of this while
they are present

6
00:00:17,396 --> 00:00:20,885
ISIS members are present,
each sitting in his place at his desk

7
00:00:23,776 --> 00:00:27,526
Their own police

8
00:00:30,521 --> 00:00:35,052
And the interrogators, I
mean the whole place is ISIS

9
00:00:35,391 --> 00:00:40,937
Each one has his own task, and
there are young men and adults

10
00:00:41,537 --> 00:00:44,480
They come here to sort
out their IDs and their affairs

11
00:00:44,506 --> 00:00:47,422
And their documents—the main
thing they take is the documents

12
00:00:53,099 --> 00:00:57,553
Interviewer: He took you from this
place and grabbed you by the hand

13
00:00:57,578 --> 00:00:58,568
Yes, by my hand

14
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:01,901
And he took me
to their interrogator

15
00:01:02,448 --> 00:01:04,115
Interviewer: Can we go there?

16
00:01:09,818 --> 00:01:11,771
There were ISIS members here

17
00:01:45,678 --> 00:01:47,917
Interviewer: What
was in this corridor?

18
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:53,724
There were people sitting,
people standing, and ISIS members

19
00:01:55,547 --> 00:02:00,860
It was like any other office
we have in Mosul

20
00:02:01,303 --> 00:02:04,219
You see people, you see
who sits, goes, and comes

21
00:02:05,808 --> 00:02:08,903
Among them are ISIS
members and ordinary citizens

22
00:02:09,355 --> 00:02:12,115
To collect their personal
papers and the like

23
00:02:12,713 --> 00:02:17,480
Interviewer: What was the atmosphere like?
What did you hear—jihadi chants, or the Quran?

24
00:02:17,505 --> 00:02:20,969
Were there screams?
Was anyone being tortured?

25
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:24,172
How was the overall atmosphere
when you entered this corridor?

26
00:02:24,197 --> 00:02:29,980
Here it was just routine—people sitting, people
here for their personal business, and so on

27
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,870
A lot of people were here

28
00:02:38,677 --> 00:02:40,631
Especially upstairs
in their prisons

29
00:02:41,568 --> 00:02:47,427
They were even torturing them—taking
them to the flogging area to flog them
